<HEADLINE> World Champion Yugoslavia Enters Final in Hong Kong Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Predrag Stojakovic collected
19 points as world champion Yugoslavia edged Canada 94-89 Monday
to enter the final of the Diamond Ball 2000 men's basketball
tournament.
</P>
<P>
In the final on Wednesday, Yugoslavia plays Australia, who
eliminated Italy 101-82 in the other match of the day.
</P>
<P>
Stojakovic, who plays for the Sacramento Kings in the United
States, was the outstanding player for the Yugoslavs.
</P>
<P>
Steve Nash was the top scorer for the Canadians with 18 points.
</P>
<P>
Both Yugoslavia and Canada beat China in the four-day
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Angola, the other team in the tourney, lost to Australia and
Italy.
</P>
<P>
The six teams are using the Hong Kong tournament as a warmup
for the forthcoming Sydney Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
