<HEADLINE> Cardenas Wins 10th Stage in Tour of Spain Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Rafael Cardenas of Spain won
the 10th stage of the Tour of Spain cycle race over 165.8
kilometers from Sabadell to La Molina on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Kelme rider clocked an unofficial time of four hours 34
minutes and 10 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Santos Gonzalez of Spain took the leader's golden jersey from
his compatriot Abraham Olano during the stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
