<HEADLINE> Liberian President Suspends Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Liberian President Charles
Taylor suspended his defense minister on Monday, accusing him of
insubordination.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here quoted a presidential statement as saying
that deputy defense minister, Sylvanus Williams, would act as
caretaker minister.
</P>
<P>
The suspension of Daniel Chea came as fighting flared between
Liberian government forces and rebels in the north since July.
</P>
<P>
Taylor accused neighboring Guinea of allowing the rebels to use
its territory as a springboard for launching attacks, but Guinea
denied the charges.
</P>
<P>
Guinea said at the weekend that unidentified gunmen from
Liberia killed 47 people and wounded 29 in a raid on a Guinea
village near their common border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
