<HEADLINE> 13 Asian Drug Dealers Arrested in Qatar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Qatari security troops
arrested on Tuesday 13 Asian drug dealers and seized a large
quantity of narcotics, news reaching here reported.
</P>
<P>
Director of Drug Combating Department at Qatar's Interior
Ministry Ahmad Al-Kuleib told a press conference in Doha, capital
of Qatar, that the seized drugs included 80 kilograms of hashish,
two kilograms of opium, a quantity of heroin and 1,133 drug pills.
</P>
<P>
Al-Kuleib said a number of the drug traffickers, whose
nationalities were not disclosed, swallowed bags containing drugs,
a method that had never been used before in drug trafficking in
Qatar.
</P>
<P>
Most of the arrested dealers entered Qatar with tourist visas,
the Kuwait News Agency reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
