<HEADLINE> Zambian Minister Calls for Assistance to Newspaper Critical of Government  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Information Minister
Newstead Zimba Tuesday called for assistance to the Post newspaper,
whose office in Lusaka was gutted by fire Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
Zimba, on an inspection tour of the newspaper, described the
destruction of the computers as a major setback in media industry
and called on well wishers to help it stand on its feet.
</P>
<P>
He urged Zambia police to speed up investigation on the
incident. Post is often critical of the government.
</P>
<P>
Zimba also called on media of the country to take precautions
and proper security measures to avoid similar incident.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the newspaper will be published continuously
despite the incident but pages will be fewer.
</P>
<P>
Computers and furniture were destroyed and part of the building
caved in. Special project manager of the newspaper Goliath
Mungonge estimated the loss at about 500,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
