<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador to Use Dollar as Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's official currency,
the sucre, will cease to exist on Saturday to give way to the
American dollar as the country has entered a dollarization process
of its economy since January 9.
</P>
<P>
Starting from September 9, sucres in bills and coins will
become invalid and cease to circulate and Ecuadorians will have to
use the American dollar bills, a government decree said.
</P>
<P>
The exchange of sucres for dollars will be done till September
9 at all private banks. From this date till March 6, 2001,
Ecuadorians will exchange their sucres only at the central bank
windows. If this period is exceeded, sucres will lose all value.
</P>
<P>
According to unofficial surveys, 76 percent of the Ecuadorian
population is unhappy with the disappearance of the sucre. And in
rural areas, many peasants do not know about dollarization or how
to use the American dollar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
