<HEADLINE> Iranian Armed Forces Attaining Self-sufficiency: Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Iranian armed forces are
attaining self-sufficiency in military hardware and aerospace
technology, Iran's navy commander Rear Admiral Abbas Mohtaj said
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Iran's navy has equipped all its vessels and bases with
domestically-made missiles, the commander was quoted by the Islamic
Republic News Agency as saying at the opening ceremony of a seminar
on aerospace technology.
</P>
<P>
The navy was dependent on foreign suppliers in repairing its
vessels and equipment before the 1979 Islamic revolution, but now
Iranian technicians can conduct overhaul, repair and reconstruction
of naval hardware independently, Mohtaj noted.
</P>
<P>
He added that Iran has been successful in a number of tests of
domestically-made aerospace equipment, which indicated that the
Iranian armed forces have attained a high level of self-
sufficiency.
</P>
<P>
The progress made by the armed forces in technology and know-how
helped develop cooperation and exchange of experience between Iran
and its Persian Gulf neighbors, Mohtaj said. The U.S., Iran's arch
rival, has long accused Tehran of threatening regional security by
developing its military power. 
</P>
