<HEADLINE> Iraq-Jordan Relations to Progress in All Fields: Vice President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Iraq believes that bilateral
relations between Iraq and Jordan will soon witness rapid progress
in all fields, the official Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Vice President Taha Yassin Ramadan made the remarks during
his meeting with the two visiting Jordanian ministers, Minister of
Trade and Industry Wasif Azar and Minister of Transport Mohammad
Kalaldeh.
</P>
<P>
