<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. General Assembly Concludes 54th Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
General Assembly concluded its 54th session on Tuesday at the
United Nations headquarters in New York.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a closing ceremony, Theo-Ben Gurirab, President of
the 54th session of the United Nations General Assembly, said the
outgoing session was the first ever session of the General
Assembly which straddled two centuries and two millennia.
</P>
<P>
Recalling the session, Gurirab said the most memorable thing
was the responsibility for preparing for the unprecedented United
Nations Millennium Summit of heads of state or government to be
held from September 6 to 8, a historic moment both for the United
Nations and humanity at large.
</P>
<P>
Gurirab said a total of three special sessions were held during
the 54th session which all adopted action-oriented declarations
and platforms for implementation, taking into consideration the
outstanding progress made by member states.
</P>
<P>
The 54th session was actively engaged in the reform of the
United Nations, especially the reform and enlargement of the
United Nations Security Council, the president said.
</P>
<P>
The debate of the reform and enlargement of the Security
Council was into its seventh year and it proved once again
impossible for member states to resolve the major sticking points:
the admission of new permanent members, the exercise of veto
powers and some problematic procedural matters, the president said.
</P>
<P>
He renewed his call for more closer and regularized cooperation,
coordination and action among main U.N. bodies, especially the
General Assembly, the Security Council, the Economic and Social
Council, and the Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The session decided to convene in 2001 a critical
intergovernmental conference on financing for development, which
is a topical subject today at the core of the current debate on
development, poverty eradication, debt cancellation, full
employment and prosperity for all, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations faces challenging times in this new century
and one of the best ways of ensuring its efficiency and
performance is for it to be provided with sufficient resources and
assured political support, Gurirab stressed.
</P>
<P>
To this end, he urged member states to pay their assessed and
legally obligatory contributions on time, in full and without
conditions.
</P>
<P>
The General Assembly, set up in 1945 under the Charter of the
United Nations, is the United Nations main deliberative organ and
provides a forum for multilateral discussion of the full range of
international issues covered by the Charter.
</P>
<P>
The Assembly comprises all members of the United Nations and
meets in regular session each year from September to December, and
thereafter as required.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations General Assembly will open its 55th session
Tuesday afternoon which is designated as the Millennium Assembly.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
