<HEADLINE> Slovakia to Hold Referendum on Early Parliamentary Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Slovak President Rudolf
Schuster on Tuesday announced that the country will hold a
referendum on November 11 to decide whether to have an early
parliamentary election, according to reports from Bratislava.
</P>
<P>
Schuster made the decision in line with petitions signed by
more than 600,000 citizens and submitted by the two opposition
parties, the Slovak National Party and the Movement For Democratic
Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
Under the Slovak Constitution, the president should support
holding a referendum on important issues concerning public
interests if no less than 350,000 citizens sign their names.
</P>
<P>
The Slovak parliament, or the National Council, is due to be
reelected in 2002 when its current four-year term expires.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, demand for an early election is strong as
struggle among political parties intensifies in the country.
</P>
