<DOCNO> XIE20000905.0046 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Persecutor Sentenced to 18 Years For Taking Bribes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A local court in Haikou, the
capital of the southernmost Hainan Province, today sentenced a
former persecutor to 18-years imprisonment for taking bribes.
</P>
<P>
Wang Deli, a former deputy procurator of the municipal
procuratorate, is also deprived of his political rights for five
years and has had 24,967 yuan of his illegal income confiscated,
according to the ruling of the Haikou Intermediate People's Court.
</P>
<P>
Wang is convicted of abusing his position for personal gain. In
one case, the former persecutor helped release a swindler on bail,
after having sex with the younger sister of the defendant.
</P>
<P>
In another case, Wang rejected the application by local police
for arresting Wang Limin who was suspected of taking public
property after Wang Deli was given 100,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
In a third case, Ye Guangsheng, a local smuggler paid the
former deputy procurator 50,000 yuan for help, when he was
arrested by the municipal procuratorate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
