<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Concludes Visit to Iceland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
REYKJAVIK, September 5 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Li
Peng concluded his visit to Iceland on Tuesday and left here in
the morning for Lithuania, the second leg of his current five-
nation visit.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day visit to Iceland, Li met with Icelandic
leaders including the president, prime minister and acting speaker
of parliament, and exchanged views with them on a wide range of
issues concerning bilateral relations, regional and international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure, Li said in a message to Icelandic leaders
that his visit to Iceland was a success as it reached the set goal
of increasing understanding, enhancing trust and friendship and
deepening bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li -- Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress -- started the five-nation visit after attending
the three-day Conference of Presiding Officers of National
Parliaments held at the Headquarters of the United Nations in New
York on September 1.
</P>
<P>
After the stay in Lithuania, Li will proceed to Estonia, Latvia
and Russia. 
</P>
