<HEADLINE> Swiss Ski Federation Suspends Former World Cup Winner Accola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland's skiing federation
suspended former World Cup winner Paul Accola Tuesday after he
turned up late for a national team promotional session.
</P>
<P>
The federation said in a statement that Swiss-Ski director Jean-
Daniel Mudry sent the 33-year-old Accola, who won the overall
World Cup title in 1992, home from the weeklong session with team
sponsors and equipment suppliers in Zermatt.
</P>
<P>
The federation noted that "In the past, Paul Accola on various
occasions fell short of the behavior that can be expected from a
great champion," adding that it will decide on his future "in the
coming week." 
</P>
