<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Supply, Marketing Cooperative Important for Rural Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- China's supply and marketing
cooperative system is a vital part of the rural economy and should
play an important role in the country's rural reform and
development, Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the third national congress of the system, he said
supply and marketing cooperatives should contribute more to the
rural economic growth since they have formed a comprehensive
business network across the country China.
</P>
<P>
China's supply and marketing cooperative system is a major
channel for rural commodities distribution, helping farmers sell
their products and providing farmers necessary materials for
production.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the system has members from 180
million rural families and has nearly 30,000 grass-root
organizations all over country.
</P>
<P>
Wen, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China Central Committee, stressed that the system should
first turn losses into profits so as to better serve farmers and
the rural economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
