<HEADLINE> Vice Premier Highlights Issue of Industrial Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Vice Premier Wu Bangguo has
urged localities to further recognize the importance and urgency
of industrial safety by implementing recent instructions by
President Jiang Zemin on the issue.
</P>
<P>
The vice premier made the remark here today at a State Council
work conference on industrial safety.
</P>
<P>
A series of major accidents which occurred in the first half of
this year drew the attention of the central leadership, Wu said,
adding that President Jiang Zemin has made specific instructions
on two of the accidents.
</P>
<P>
Two national teleconferences on the issue have been held and
urgent circulars were published demanding effective measures to be
adopted by local governments to curb the occurrence of major
accidents, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
A number of unsafe factories and mines as well as recreational
facilities have been closed down because they are considered
dangerous, he said.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the months of July and August
witnessed 16 major accidents, each claiming 10 and more lives at
once, killing a total of 307 people, down by 25 percent and 19.9
percent respectively. 
</P>
