<HEADLINE> Guangdong to Expand Science Cooperation with Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Scientific and technological
cooperation between Guangdong Province, Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan will be promoted, said an official of the Guangdong
provincial government today.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong has made a plan to enhance scientific cooperation as
a part of the province's strategy of development through science
and education, said Ma Xianmin, deputy director of the provincial
science and technology department.
</P>
<P>
Although no definite cooperation agreement has been reached
among the local governments, non-governmental scientific
cooperation between Guangdong, Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan has
increased day by day, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the 1980s, enterprises from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan only
invested in the processing sector in Guangdong. However, in recent
years, more and more research and development institutions under
the enterprises entered Guangdong, employing a large number of
researchers from the mainland, said Ma.
</P>
<P>
High-tech projects in the province have become the target of
venture capital from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan. At the same time,
a number of high-tech enterprises in Guangzhou and Shenzhen cities
are ready to be listed in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The official also expressed the belief that Macao will become a
bridge between Guangdong and Europe in further economic and
scientific cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
