<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Journalists Win Copyright Lawsuit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A group of local journalists
in Beijing have won a lawsuit over the infringement of their
copyright by the China Opera and Drama Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The district court of Haidian, in western Beijing, today issued
a ruling demanding the publishing house to apologize and
compensate the reporters.
</P>
<P>
According to the court, the defendant published a collection of
70 stories on the life of local residents in Beijing and it became
a best seller.
</P>
<P>
Of the 70 stories, 64 were found to be "downloaded" from
several issues of a local magazine, involving 32 local journalists.
</P>
<P>
The angry reporters sued the publishing house and won. The
publisher has been ordered to make a public apology and pay 300
yuan per thousand characters to the original authors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
