<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Yoshiro
Mori left here for New York on Tuesday evening to participate the
three-day U.N. Millennium Summit starting from Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a scheduled five-minute speech to the summit on Thursday,
Mori will call for an increase in both permanent and nonpermanent
seats of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
