<DOCNO> XIE20000905.0078 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Down in EU in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in the
European Union (EU) went further down to 8.3 percent in July while
the jobless rate in the euro zone remained unchanged at 9.1
percent, Eurostat reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical agency of the European
Community said the lowest unemployment rate was registered in
Luxembourg which was 2.2 percent, while the highest was posted in
Spain which stood at 14.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to Eurostat figures, unemployment fell in all EU
member states in July, with the biggest falls registered in the
Netherlands (from 3.4 percent to 2.6 percent), Ireland (from 5.7
percent to 4.5 percent), Sweden (from 7.1 percent to 5.6 percent),
France (from 11.3 percent to 9.6 percent) and Austria (from 3.8
percent to 3.2 percent).
</P>
<P>
Observers regarded the falls in unemployment as a sign for
sound economic growth in both the EU and the euro zone. The EU has
suffered from the problem of unemployment in the past two decades
when some of its member states hit double-digit jobless rates.
</P>
<P>
At the Lisbon summit held last March, the EU decided to boost
employment through knowledge-based new economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
