<HEADLINE> Cameroon Olympic Soccer Team Loses Five Key Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Cameroon's Olympic soccer team
lost five key players on the eve of the Sydney Olympics, the
African champions' coach said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Paul Akono told state radio that notable absentees in
Sydney would include Joseph Desire Job, who is concentrating on
building a career at new club Middlesborough, Salomon Olembe of
Nantes who is absent for personal reasons and St. Etienne's Lucien
Metomo, out with injury.
</P>
<P>
Olympique Lyon midfielder Marc-Vivien Foe will also be absent,
as will Rigobert Song, whom Liverpool coach Gerard Houllier is
refusing to release because of important premier league games in
September.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon are expected to leave for Australia on September 9.
The team is currently training in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon will play Kuwait in their first match on September 13,
two days before the official start of the Olympic Games, in
Brisbane. 
</P>
