<HEADLINE> East China Tax Payers to Turn in Taxes On-line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Provincial Telecom
Company (SPTC) and the Shandong Taxation Administrative Bureau (
STAB) have signed a contract today to realize 90 percent of tax
payers turning in taxes via the Internet or telephone by the first
quarter of next year.
</P>
<P>
STAB director Song Lan said the new ways of tax payment will
save the time and simplify procedures, thus lowering costs.
</P>
<P>
The SPTC has developed a new tax payment system to ensure the
security of on-line or phone call tax payment. By August, nearly 2,
000 enterprises have used the new system to pay taxes by phone
calls and 170 via the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Managing staff with the SPTC said they also set a specific tax
payment phone service number "17961" for the tax payers in the
province. They are striving to soon connect with the State
Administration of Taxation, joining in the national taxation
network. 
</P>
