<DOCNO> XIE20000905.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Bill Drafted to Ensure HK's Market Transparency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Securities and Futures
Bill, 2000 will be aimed to ensure the market transparency while
minimizing the burden of disclosure as much as possible, said the
chief of Hong Kong Securities and Futures Commission (SFC) here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We feel that disclosure is necessary to give a complete
picture, but, on the other hand, we recognize that we do not wish
to impose excessively burdensome reporting requirements on the
market," said Andrew Sheng, chairman of the SFC.
</P>
<P>
The bill, which was drafted to set up a regulatory framework to
strengthen Hong Kong's status as an international financial center,
will be submitted to the Legislative Council in November.
</P>
<P>
The bill aims to protect the investors as well as market users
and intermediaries and to accommodate new regulatory, legal and
policy issues and the rapid advance of technology seen in the last
few years, said Sheng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
