<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yemeni Police Defuse Mine in Front of Tax Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni security forces have
defused a mine laid in a sewer in front of Sanaa Tax Office,
according to a security source on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The security forces were combing the area for a possible second
mine, the source said.
</P>
<P>
Local police were tipped on Monday night by an unidentified
source that two people had laid the two mines in the sewer, he
noted.By defusing the mine, the area was saved from a blast which
could have caused casualties and property losses, he added.
</P>
<P>
No details were disclosed about the identity of the perpetrators
or the reasons for their plot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
