<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Parts of South India State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The tremor, which occurred at 6:02 a.m. Tuesday and measured 5.
0 on the Richter scale, caused damage to many houses and panic
among the people, but no loss of life was reported, said the PTI.
</P>
<P>
Mild tremors were also felt in the neighboring states of Goa
and Karnataka, the PTI added.
</P>
<P>
According to the local meteorology department, the exact
location of the quake was placed at 17.3 latitude and 73.8
longitude in Koyna region.
</P>
<P>
The shock is the eighth high-intensity quake since 1963 in the
state, whose capital Mumbai is India's key port and financial and
entertainment center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
