<HEADLINE> Xinhua Summary of Asia-Pacific Stocks News on September 5 Xinhua Summary of Asia-Pacific Stocks News on September 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI -- The Composite Index on the Shanghai Stock Exchange
closed at 1963.79 points Tuesday, down 46.81 points from the
previous session, according to the Guangfa Securities Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
SHENZHEN -- The Component Stock Index on the Shenzhen Stock
Exchange closed at 4723.07 points Tuesday, down 94.86 points from
the previous session, according to the Guangfa Securities Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
HONG KONG -- Hong Kong stocks lost 130.95 points, or 0.74
percent, to close at 17,595.22 Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was light at 8.698 billion HK dollars (1.115 billion U.
S. dollars), compared with Monday's 11.091 billion HK dollars (1.
422 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index went up 0.75 percent to 2,859.60 and
Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index rose 1.70 percent to 3,487.50.
</P>
