<HEADLINE> Angolan Government Troops Repel Rebel Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government troops
and the local security forces have repelled an attack reportedly
launched by a rebel group on the fuel storage facility located in
the central highland city of Huambo, the Portuguese news agency
Lusa reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
No casualties or material damages resulted from the attack,
which took place in the Vila Graca neighborhood and lasted some 10
minutes, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The incident is the second armed attack in less than one week
by presumed rebels of the National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola led by Jonas Savimbi.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the rebels made an incursion into the Canhe
neighborhood, but were defeated by the local security forces.
</P>
</TEXT>
