<HEADLINE> Dynamo Kiev Sign Russian for Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian champions Dynamo Kiev
have signed Russia under-23 international Vladimir Kuzmichyov to
strengthen their team for the Champions League.
</P>
<P>
Dynamo vice-president Josef Sabo Tuesday said: "We expect him
to arrive in Kiev today and begin training with us right away as
we have high hopes and expectations for him."
</P>
<P>
Sabo refused to give contract details for the 21-year-old
midfielder but said it was a long-term deal.
</P>
<P>
Dynamo, European Cup semifinalists in 1999, were paired in the
Champions League first phase with Anderlecht, PSV Eindhoven and
Manchester United. 
