<HEADLINE> UEFA Says Leicester Will Play in Belgrade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 5 (Xinhua) -- European soccer's governing
body UEFA insisted Tuesday that English club Leicester must play
an upcoming match in Belgrade despite warnings of potential civil
unrest in Yugoslavia by the British Foreign Office.
</P>
<P>
leicester's Sept. 28 UEFA Cup match against Red Star Belgrade
is scheduled four days after a general election.
</P>
<P>
A UEFA spokesman said that the match is still scheduled and
that local authorities are expected to adequately safeguard
players and officials.
</P>
<P>
However, if the situation changed in Yugoslavia, the spokesman
suggested that a postponement was possible.
</P>
<P>
"This game takes place four days after the elections, roughly
when the results come out," the spokesman noted. 
</P>
