<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France-Germany Soccer Match Fixed for February 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The soccer friendly match
between World and European champions France and bitter rivals
Germany was rescheduled for February 27 at The Stade de France,
The French soccer federation announced here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The match was originally scheduled for the Wednesday but the
Stadium was already booked.
</P>
<P>
Revised schedule:
</P>
<P>
October 4: Cameroon (Stade de France)
</P>
<P>
October 7: South Africa (Johannesburg)
</P>
<P>
November 15: Turkey (Istanbul)
</P>
<P>
2001
</P>
<P>
February 27: Germany (Stade de France)
</P>
<P>
March 24: European opponent to be decided (venue in France to
be announced)
</P>
<P>
