<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Painting Delights American Social Activist (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese-American social
activist Anna Chan Chennault today expressed her delight with a
portrait of her husband presented to her by the Luzhou Painting
Studio in Southwest China's Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
The two-meter by one-meter painting, titled "Portrait of
General Chennault", is a meticulous-style Chinese work done in
colors of oil-painting style. In the picture, Mr. Chennault is
wearing a dark-green army suit, with three-star general shoulder
marks. His facial expression is solemn but fire-eyed.
</P>
<P>
The artist, Wei Wensheng, said he spent six months on the
portrait, which was done on dacron cloth.
</P>
<P>
He said that he created the painting based on Mr. Chennault's
photos and other reference materials offered by Mrs. Chennault.
</P>
<P>
Wei Wensheng also painted a portrait of Mrs. Chennault titled "
Herald of Spring", which was presented to Mrs. Chennault on
September 30 last year.
</P>
<P>
"I had never seen Chennault in person, but relied on a photo
and her autobiography to re-create her likeness," the painter said,
adding that the painting, which is a meticulous-style Chinese work
done in soft colors, was taken back to Washington by Mrs.
Chennault and is on display in the conference center of the
Council for International Cooperation of the U.S.
</P>
<P>
"The portrait of Mr. Chennault" will be displayed in the
private museum of Mrs. Chennault in the office building of the
Council for International Cooperation of the U.S.
</P>
<P>
The museum collection mainly consists of photos, paintings, and
documents and materials about the "Flying Tigers" and the Anti-
Japanese War.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Chennault's husband, General Claire Lee Chennault, was
commander of the U.S. 14th Air Fleet during World War II. He
organized a group of American pilots, known as the "Flying Tigers,
" who transported arms and other materials, and joined in an air
raid supporting China against Japanese invaders.
</P>
</TEXT>
