<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Average Beverage Consumption to Double in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Average beverage consumption
in China will double in five years, according to an official
source.
</P>
<P>
By 2005, beverage consumption in China will be 20 kilograms,
and beverage output will be 27 million tons, up 14 percent every
year.
</P>
<P>
In the past ten years, ten types of beverage including soda pop,
mineral water and ade, have replaced the former one and the only
beverage -- soda pop in China.
</P>
<P>
At present, the annual beverage output by domestic
manufactories has reached 20 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Beverage output and consumption will continue to rise with
increases in income, experts said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the demand for healthy, natural, low-in-sugar
beverages is increasing, which will promote the growth of new
types of beverages.
</P>
<P>
China's annual consumption of ade, which is one kilogram per
person, is low compared with the world average annual consumption
of seven kilograms.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, beverage output and
consumption in China will greatly increase whenever new types of
beverages emerge, experts say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
