<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Helps Poverty-Stricken Elderly People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A total of 15,000 poverty-
stricken elderly people in China have received government-
sponsored living assistance since the country launched its aid-the-
elderly project four years ago.
</P>
<P>
A symposium was held here today to celebrate the project's
fourth anniversary.
</P>
<P>
The China Association for Aged People and the China Senior
Citizens Fund, which jointly initiated the project, have launched
a series of activities to support the elderly, including building
homes and public welfare clinics for poverty-stricken elderly
people in 20 provinces, municipalities and ethnic autonomous
regions.
</P>
<P>
The project also called for social forces to provide assistance
for elderly people.
</P>
<P>
Community service networks will be promoted to aid the poor old
people, based on the experience of one built up in Beijing's
Panjiayuan street, according to sources with the symposium.
</P>
<P>
Free medicines, physical check-ups and other medical services
are also provided to the old people. Up to June this year, the
project had provided free physical check-ups for over 100,000
elderly people, and carried out a series of programs focusing on
the health of elderly people, particularly treating cataract,
diabetes and other common diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
