<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Troops Exchange Fire With Burundian Rebels Along Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian People's
Defense Forces (TPDF) exchanged fire briefly with Burundian armed
rebels along the two countries' border last week, the independent
Guardian newspaper reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Burundian rebels were fleeing fierce fighting with the
government troops in Burundi's southern Makamba Province, which is
near the Tanzanian border, the newspaper quoted reliable sources
from the western Kigoma region as saying.
</P>
<P>
The sources hinted that after being trounced by the Burundi
government soldiers, armed rebels ran towards the common border in
an attempt to cross into Tanzania's Kigoma region. However, they
were sent back by TPDF soldiers, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The sources further said that the Burundian Defense Minister
Cyrille Ndairukiye will meet his Tanzanian counterpart Edgar
Majogo in Kigoma region soon to discuss last week's brief fire
exchange along the common border. 
</P>
