<HEADLINE> China's T-bond Market Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond market closed
mixed today.
</P>
<P>
Three bonds rose while three dropped during thin trading over
the day, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial
and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Transaction value totaled 1.31 billion yuan, comparing with 944
million yuan on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The newly issued floating-rate bond 010004 dipped 0.11 percent
to 104.48 yuan after rallying on Monday. The yield of the bond
rose 0.01 percentage point to 2.41 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009704 (9.78 percent, due 2007) ended at 135.39 yuan, down
0.08 percent from the market reference price. Transactions in the
bond stayed thin during the day, with a volume of 58 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Among the top losers, bond 009908 (3.3 percent, due 2009)
jumped by 0.14 percent to 103.00 yuan, and bond 000896 (8.56
percent, due 2003) and bond 009905 (3.28 percent, due 2007) rose 0.
05 percent respectively. 
