<HEADLINE> Shanghai A Shares Dives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
closed at 1,963.79 points Tuesday, down 46.81 points or 2.33
percent from the last close.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 8.71 billion yuan, 7.34 percent less than
Monday's 9.4 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Composite Index jumped to 2,015.06 points shortly
after opening but was driven down soon by heavy selling above the
2,100-point level.
</P>
<P>
The index dived abruptly below the 1,980-point level shortly
before closing and broke the bottom line of the past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Homeway experts said that the investors are increasingly
concerned about the market due to a rally in the IPO market and
rumors about the launch of a second board market.
</P>
<P>
Among the top winners Tuesday, Shanghai Lingqiao Tap Water Co.,
Ltd. gained 5.02 percent to close at 25.94 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Port Machinery was the top loser after exercising the
ex-rights dividends, dipping 7.03 percent to close at 16 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Homeway predicts that the A-share market is to stabilize at a
new support line Wednesday. 
