<HEADLINE> Famous Chinese-American Awards Chinese Teachers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Wang Hongxia, a teacher from
northwest China's Gansu Province along with 211 other teachers
received the second "Anna Chan Chennault Education Award for
Teachers of Pre-school, Primary and Secondary Schools" today in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The award is donated by Anna Chan Chennault, a Chinese-American
and President of the U.S. Committee for International Cooperation.
Chennault set up the China Awards (Education) Foundation for
Teachers of Pre-school, Primary and Secondary Schools.
</P>
<P>
All the 212 teachers were recommended and chosen by award
foundations from the provinces and autonomous regions they belong
to. Most of the teachers come from Gansu, Qinghai, Guizhou and
Yunnan provinces and the autonomous regions of Inner Mongolia,
Ningxia Hui, Xinjiang Uygur, Guangxi Zhuang and Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The teachers were keen on teaching in rural and mountainous
areas, and have made a great contribution to the teaching
profession in China. This award aims to commend their selfless
dedication.
</P>
<P>
Vice Education Minister Wei Yu thanked Anna Chan Chennault for
her efforts in promoting Sino-U.S. relations and called for all of
China's teachers to learn from these teachers.
</P>
<P>
Anna Chan Chennault said that she will do her best to help
promote education in China, as well as push forward social
progress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
