BEIJING -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC) announced today
that it will liberalize the lending rate of foreign currencies
starting from September 21.
</P>
<P>
Major reform measures are also made simultaneously on the
deposit rate of foreign currencies, according to the PBOC, the
central bank. 
