<DOCNO> XIE20000905.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Opens First Robotics Learning Center in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Robotics Learning Center, a 1.2 million Singapore dollar (
about 0.7 million U.S. dollars) project, targets both primary and
secondary students.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Singapore Education Minister
Teo Chee Hean said the center aims to inspire students to develop
self-confidence, creativity, and skills of using robotics and new
technology.
</P>
<P>
"In the emerging knowledge-based economy, creativity,
innovation, inventiveness and resilience are essential attributes
for all our pupils," Teo said.
</P>
<P>
At the center, students will be able to gain an elementary
knowledge about robotics and engage in the design and building of
robots, said an employee at the Singapore Discovery Center which
hosts the Robotics facility.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said that they expect the center to attract about 35,
000 visitors each year. 
</P>
