<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-Share Market Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share Index
dropped 1.94 points or 2.38 percent to 66.65 points on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 24.25 million U.S. dollars, or 18.06 percent up
from Monday's total, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market entered a phase of correction after the robust rally
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts said that the market is still weak after a
climbing out of a week-long tumble last week.
</P>
<P>
Forty-seven shares dropped, four rose and four remained
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Among the top winners, China Travel gained 4.52 percent to
close at 0.412 U.S. dollars. Ji'nan Qingqi climbed 2.48 percent to
0.248 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Airlines lost 6.97 percent to close 0.412 U.S. dollars.
Another big loser is Shanghai Huili, falling 0.312 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Homeway predicts that the market may chisel out minor gains in
the session ahead and linger around the current level. 
