<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Firms Establishes Venture to Commercialize Gallium Arsenide Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Institute of
Semiconductors with the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) and four
other companies signed an agreement here today to commercialize
the institute's semi-insulated gallium arsenide technology.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the agreement will bring about 100 million
to 200 million U.S. dollars in export earnings for China.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the Compound Crystal Technology Co., Ltd.
will be set up by the five entities with a registered capital of
100 million yuan (about 12 million U.S. dollars), including
technology valued at 30 million yuan (about 3.6 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The five entities, including the China Energy Conservation
Investment Corporation, plan to invest 300 to 400 million yuan (
about 36 million to 48 million U.S. dollars) in importing
production equipment and building a plant.
</P>
<P>
The planned plant, the only one of its kind in China, is
expected to produce single crystal and epitaxial wafers of semi-
insulated gallium arsenide, which are expensive materials for
integrated circuits used in optical fiber and mobile
telecommunications products, such as mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
Li Jin-min, assistant director of the institute, said the five
partners plan to have the joint venture listed on the stock market
as soon as it is approved by government departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000905.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Introduces Electronic Fraud Detection System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Finance Ministry has
commissioned a special computer program to combat invoice and
export fraud crimes, reported Turkish Daily News on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the program, called the deterrent Early Warning
System, Ankara will be alerted immediately if a tax office which
has a definite annual turnover approves an export tax rebate of an
extraordinary sum of money on a single day.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, Ankara will be automatically alerted if a businessman
who pays certain amount of money in corporation tax a year receives
an unusual sum of value-added tax rebate all of a sudden.
</P>
<P>
Fikret Sevinc, the Finance Ministry director general for
accounting in charge of the project, said that in such cases, the
computers will not only flash a red light but also issue an audible
warning.
</P>
<P>
The system was adopted after waves of invoice and export fraud
cases occurred in the country's customs offices, which had caused
the country losses of million of U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In Izmir, southwest Turkey last week, police launched a drive
code-named Operation Whale and foiled an export fraud, which
involved 30 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Also uncovered during the operation was an invoice fraud
involving a total of sum of 110 trillion Turkish liras (roughly 180
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
By now 52 people have been detained. The clues have led to
certain high-level bureaucrats in Ankara. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000905.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Barak Rejects Israeli Army's Budget Demands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Ehud Barak had
rejected Israeli army budget demands for a real-term hike of 250
million U.S. dollars in the 2001 fiscal year, the Ha'aretz daily
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister, now in New York for the United Nations
Millennium Summit and a critical meeting with United States
President Bill Clinton, had made the decision before he departure
Sunday night, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Israel Defense Forces argued that under an agreement with
the Finance Ministry last December, it should get back the 250
million U.S. dollars deducted from this year's budget.
</P>
<P>
However, the Treasury vehemently rejected the IDF demands,
saying the army had financially benefited from the withdrawal from
south Lebanon this May, which could amount to 375 million dollars a
year according to various estimates.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with Finance Ministry officials and IDF Chief of
General Staff Shaul Mofaz, Barak shifted his earlier support for
the army's demands to the Treasury's position.
</P>
<P>
This settled the 2001 budget for defense to 36.3 billion shekels
(about 9.1 billion dollars), 195 million dollars more than this
year's budget. However, the real-term increase will only be 22.5
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The budget bill, which will be debated in Israel's Knesset
(parliament) after it's summer recess ends late October, had not
been finalized.
</P>
<P>
The bill will be put to a parliamentary vote in December and
seems difficult to get the endorsement because the Barak government
now controls only one-third seats in the 120-member legislature.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
