<HEADLINE> Rebels Kill 8 in Northern Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Eight disco revellers were
killed and six others injured by the Lord's Resistance Army (LRA)
rebels of Joseph Kony in northern Uganda's Kitgum district, the
New Vision daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 503 Brigade Commander of the Uganda People's Defence Forces
Richard Kiwanuka confirmed that eight people were killed and about
six injured on Friday by five LRA rebels, said the report.
</P>
<P>
"The Red Cross brought some to the hospital," said Kiwanuka,
adding that "the LRA rebels have lost ground and are desperate and
angry that the civilians are not supporting or cooperating with
them."
</P>
<P>
A total of 18 people were killed by the LRA between August 30
and September 2, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
