<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-Share Market Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-Share Index
dipped 2.89 points, or 2.39 percent to close at 118.26 points on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover dwindled to 88.5 million HK dollars, 10.93
million HK dollars or 10.99 percent less than Monday's total,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market managed to rally shortly this afternoon. But selling
pressure forced it down to an intraday low of 117.96 points.
</P>
<P>
Breadth figures pointed to the negative end as losers out
numbered by 50 to four. Two stocks remained unchanged today.
</P>
<P>
Livzon Pharm rose 4.2 percent to close at 2.48 HK dollars,
while Weifu Fuel rose 2.03 percent to 3.52 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sez Real Estate and Zhonglu topped the losers list, dropping by
4.76 percent and 4.64 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts say that the Shenzhen B-share market is likely
to see fluctuations in trading on Wednesday. The market will
remain in the stage of correction, with no positive turn in sight.
</P>
</TEXT>
