<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reiterates Firm Opposition to U.S. NMD Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- China today voiced again its
firm opposition to the National Missile Defense (NMD) program of
the United States.
</P>
<P>
When answering a question at a press conference this afternoon,
Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi urged the US to go along the
trend of the time, carefully listen to the just appeal of the
international community, and completely abandon its anti-missile
plans at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that the U.S. development of advanced anti-missile
systems, in the form of the NMD or the Theater Missile Defense (
TMD), is designed to ensure its own absolute security and the
freedom of action, and to seek a U.S.-led mono-polar world.
</P>
<P>
He said that such an attempt will undermine the global and
regional strategic balance and stability, and get the process of
international arms control and disarmament and anti-proliferation
deadlocked, and even reverse the process and lead to a new round
of arms race in the world.
</P>
<P>
"The prospects of the matter are detrimental to all the
countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Many countries have expressed concerns about the U.S. attempt
to develop anti-missile systems, and some of its allies also
expressed doubt and unrest, Sun said, adding that such an attempt
is also opposed by Americans.
</P>
<P>
"All these demonstrate that the U.S. anti-missile plans are
unpopular," the spokesman stated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
