<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Typhoon Maring Leaves 3 Dead in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed,
hundreds of commuters stranded and scores of vehicles stalled as
continuous rain spawned by typhoon Maring flooded many parts of
Metro Manila Tuesday morning, Philippine News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Two of the victims were from Caloocan City and the third from
Quezon City, all in Metro Manila. The victims died of cardiac
arrest when flood waters began to rise in her house.
</P>
<P>
The rain lashed Metro Manila and nearby provinces continuously
for six hours beginning at midnight and the flood rose up to more
than 5 feet in some streets.
</P>
<P>
Classes were suspended in all level in Metro Manila and victims
of heavy flooding were evacuated to public schools.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, relief rescue operations also started in eight
flooded towns in Pampanga province.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Disaster Coordinating Council (PDCC) reported
that at least two four-year-old children drowned during the floods.
</P>
<P>
The PDCC said the victims were asleep when floodwaters rose
during heavy rains spawned by the tropical storm.
</P>
<P>
The PDCC also reported that 74 villages in the eight flooded
towns remained under four to five feet deep of floodwaters as of
Tuesday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
