<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Inflation Rate Up to 4.6 Percent in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine year-on-year
inflation rate rose to 4.6 percent in August from 4.3 percent in
July mainly due to increased fuel price, the government said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The National Statistics Office (NSO) said in a press release
that the month-on-month inflation in food, beverage and tobacco
and services also increased by 0.7 percent over the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the inflation came as fuel price increase pushed
up the cost of living and the peso extended its slide against the
U.S.dollar.
</P>
<P>
The pickup in inflation "doesn't ring any alarm bells," said
Erico Claudio, a local market researcher. "We've been used to much
higher rates in the past."
</P>
<P>
According to the NSO, the inflation rate a year ago was 5.5
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
