<HEADLINE> Grape Center to Celebrate Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Huailai County, in north China
's Hebei province, known as one of China's grape-producing center,
is going to celebrate its bumper grape harvest from September 9
through October 5.
</P>
<P>
During the period, visitors may pick grapes in orchards, visit
the wine factories and taste wines.
</P>
<P>
The climate in Huailai basin has made it an appropriate place
for cultivating grape for almost 800 years. The Sanggan River
valley in the county, covering an area of 2,000 square kilometers,
is praised by agricultural experts as favorable for grape growing,
and rivals Bordeaux in France.
</P>
<P>
Since 1976, when the county was designated as a national grape
base, grape production there has significantly increased.
</P>
<P>
Its current annual output stands at 57,000 tons, with a sales
income of 180 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
