<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Singapore to Initiate Cultural Exchange Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Singapore
have agreed to initiate cultural exchange programs to forge closer
ties between the people of the two neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
An agreement in this regard was reached recently in a special
meeting attended by senior officials of the Malaysian Culture,
Arts and Tourism Ministry and the Singapore Culture Council, the
Bernama news agency reported Tuesday quoting Culture, Arts and
Tourism Minister Abdul Kadir Sheikh Fadzir.
</P>
<P>
"Cultural exchange programs are ongoing but not many. They are
initiated on an ad-hoc basis with no proper planning. After this,
we'll plan it well and do it more seriously," Abdul Kadir was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Under the programs, cultural troupes from Malaysia and
Singapore would stage performances in each other's country.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also agreed to share the cost for
inviting drama groups from overseas particularly from western
countries to perform in Malaysia and Singapore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
