<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Online Marketplace for Chemical Products Launched in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A secure online
marketplace,known as WorldSol.com, for chemical and chemical
related products and services trading, was launched here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The WorldSol.com Sdn Bhd, the owner of the closed business to
business chemical exchange, has 8 founding members of leading
chemical companies and more partners from Thailand, Indonesia and
the Philippines are expected to join the company soon, the company
's chief executive officer Siew Ka Wei told reporters at the
launching.
</P>
<P>
Through WorldSol.com, members can showcase, buy, sell, auction,
reverse auction and search for products, new services, new
customers and new suppliers at any time and from anywhere.
</P>
<P>
WorldSol.com will offer a catalogue of over 6,000 products
covering industrial chemical, gases, petroleum products and
plastic as well as a range of related equipment and services to
cater to the needs of all chemical industry players, he said.
</P>
<P>
WorldSol.com operates on a framework and technology provided by
Oracle which presently powers over 90 percent of world e-business
solutions. 
</P>
