<HEADLINE> Philippine Peso Breaks 45.50:1 Level vs. Greenback </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine peso breached
the crucial 45.50:1 support level against the U.S. dollar early
Tuesday as sentiment on the peso remained low.
</P>
<P>
The peso averaged 45.489, weaker to Monday's close of 45.300.
</P>
<P>
It opened at 45.400, immediately hitting a low of 45.595 in
early trade.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said banks held onto their dollars on expectation the
peso would weaken further due to the lingering worries over the
budget deficit and the insurgency problem in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
"It's sentiment driven, you can really tell the market is
afraid to short sell the dollar," said a trader at a local bank.
</P>
<P>
Value of trade turnover reached 112 million dollars in mid-
trade.
</P>
