<HEADLINE> China's First-Grade Teachers Receive Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Teachers of China's first-
grade primary and high school students were recently trained on
the revised teaching materials, according to today's "Guangming
Daily".
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education first trained the administrators,
principals and senior teachers, followed by all other teachers
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The revised books include a compilation of new subject
standards and teaching books, and the revision of current teaching
outlines and books in high schools and the 9-year compulsory
education period.
</P>
<P>
Training subjects for senior high school teachers include
teaching plans, goals, research methods of the revised courses and
outlines, and education reform in foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Revision and revised content will be the focus of training of
primary and junior high school teachers.
</P>
<P>
Experts who revised the teaching materials and publishers from
the People's Education Press will take charge of the training
program.
</P>
<P>
Revised course outlines and books for seven high schools
subjects have been used in ten provinces and cities since the
start of September. Revised course outlines for 16 compulsory
subjects and books in primary grades have been used in the whole
country since September 1.  
</P>
</TEXT>
