were enrolled, 1,690 more than the number set beforehand by
colleges and universities in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Schools with more candidates than ever before have had to
revise their original plan and increased their enrollment quota,
the paper explained.
</P>
<P>
To prevent corruption during the course of enrollment, 158
higher education schools have experimented with enrolling students
through the Internet, with 27,000 students enrolled this way,
according to the paper. 
