<HEADLINE> U.N. Jail Officer Suspended for Prisoners Escape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Bernard Kouchner, the head of
Kosovo's U.N. administration, announced Monday in the Kosovo
capital Pristina that the U.N. police director of the jail in
Kosovska Mitrovica was suspended after prisoners escaped late
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav news agency Tanjug reported that the officer comes
from a central-America country.
</P>
<P>
Late Sunday, 15 Serb prisoners escaped from the jail and two of
them were recaptured immediately, but 13 others remain at large,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Kouchner, the special representative of the U.N. Secretary-
General for Kosovo, was quoted as saying that "I feel humiliated,
frustrated and guilty," adding he wanted the U.N. staff to be
responsible for their mission.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, on Sunday afternoon some Serbs in the northern
Kosovska Mitrovica blocked the jail and the roads to the city to
stop the police to transfer the Serb prisoners.
</P>
<P>
The local Serbs believed that the imprisoned Serbs were accused
falsely of war crime by ethnic Albanians. Many of them have been
in jail for more than one year but have so far not been put on
trial. 
</P>
