<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, September 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- The first European Conference for Electronic Trade
opened in Bucharest on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"This conference belongs to a wave of preoccupations by the
Central and Eastern European countries, and its main target is
both the estimation of the commitment level of the education and
research staff in this trade's development, as well as the
improvement of the international relations in the field," the
director of the Electronic Trade Initiative Center, Professor
Gheorghe Sandulescu said at the conference.
</P>
<P>
