- - - -
</P>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Three oil pipelines in Colombia,
which export more than 200,000 barrels of oil daily, are out of
service due to guerrilla sabotage, said the state-owned oil
company Ecopetrol.
</P>
<P>
The most seriously affected pipeline, the Cano Limon-Covel
pipeline, which once pumped 105,000 barrels of oil daily, has
operated only 80 hours since July 23 because of 24 dynamite
attacks by the National Liberation Army (ELN) and the
Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC). (Colombia-Oil
Pipelines-Guerrilla Attack)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
