island on Tuesday, said at a press conference that his stay here
helped intensify relations not only politically, but in every
social and commercial aspect.
</P>
<P>
As to economic ties, Lukashenko revealed that Minsk will
provide Havana with 200,000 tons of oil in exchange for 180,000
tons of fertilizer, 100,000 tons of potassium, and urea.
</P>
<P>
"This is only the first step," said Lukashenko, who revealed
that both countries are carrying out economic projects to exchange
various goods, adding that in his country it is possible to set up
a pharmaceutical plant. (Cuba-Belarussia-Cooperation)
</P>
