<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Give Award to Foreign Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing in southwest China
will honor foreign experts working in the city with the "Three
Gorges Friendship Award" for their outstanding contributions.
</P>
<P>
The award is a branch of "Friendship Award", China's highest
for foreign experts which was set up in 1991. Prior to Chongqing,
36 provinces and cities had established similar awards with a
variety of titles.
</P>
<P>
According to a foreign affairs official, the city will present
the award to five foreign experts per year who have made great
contributions to local economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing is the country's fourth municipality that is near the
famous Three Gorges Area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
