<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guizhou to Host Ethnic Garment Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guizhou
Province will host a major cultural festival displaying ethnic
groups wearing traditional garments on October 3-4.
</P>
<P>
The festival will feature a dozen ethnic groups including, Miao,
Yao, Shui and Zhuang, said a local cultural official.
</P>
<P>
Many of the ethnic groups, especially the Miao and Dong ethnic
groups, have rare and special dress styles, ornaments, handicrafts
and arts, according to the official,
</P>
<P>
The population of Miao and Dong ethnic groups living in Guizhou
account for 28 and 38 percent respectively of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The provincial culture department and the tourism bureau will
jointly sponsor the two-day event in Kaili, capital of the
Qiandongnan Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Also on display are an ethnic garment exhibition, art
performance, dress show, seminars on ethnic culture, tourism and
economic development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
