<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Killed in Indonesia's Aceh After Truce Renewal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Four rebels were killed in
Aceh, Indonesia, on Sunday, just one day after the government and
Free Aceh Movement (GAM) extended their three-month cease-fire
agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Observer Tuesday quoted local police chief
Lieutenant Colonel Endang Emiqail Bagus as saying three rebels
were killed on Sunday during a 30-minute gunbattle in the north of
the province.
</P>
<P>
He said the fight took place after a failed ambush attempt
against a convoy of police trucks passing through Pidie's Mutiara
subdistrict. Police had seized two automatic rifles, a handgun and
more than 300 bullets from the victims.
</P>
<P>
In another incident, a rebel was shot dead when allegedly
planting bombs in Deah Pangwa village in Pidie district.
</P>
<P>
The death brought to 75 the number of people killed in Aceh
since the original three-month truce went into effect on June 2.
Each side has blamed the other for the bloodshed while pledging to
maintain support for the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed last Saturday to extend the Joint
Understanding on Humanitarian Pause for one month while preparing
for a new round of peace talks in mid-September in Geneva,
Switzerland, where the initial deal was struck. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
