<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives for U.N. Millennium Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin arrived here this evening to participate in the Millennium
summit of the United Nations (U.N.) scheduled from September 6 to
8.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang was warmly greeted at the airport by the
resident Chinese officials and hundreds of overseas Chinese and
Chinese Americans at the Waldorf-Astorial hotel, where Jiang will
stay.
</P>
<P>
During the event, the Chinese president will also attend the
summit of the U.N. Security Council and deliver a speech on issues
such as maintaining world peace and security.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang will also meet with leaders of some countries
for an exchange of views on issues of bilateral relations as well
as those of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The Millennium summit, an important event for the United
Nations, will focus on "the role of the United Nations in the 21st
century." Other important strategic issues, such as the direction
of the United Nations, the position and role of the United Nations
in establishing a new international political and economic order,
will also be closely watched by all nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
