<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Light Plane Crashes in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A light plane crashed early
Tuesday morning in Queensland in the northeast of Australia.
</P>
<P>
All eight people on board were believed to have been killed,
the Australian Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The plane ignited on impact and caused a bushfire in a remote
area.
</P>
<P>
The twin-engine prop plane, chartered by one of Australia's
largest gold producers, was flying to the West Australian Gold
Fields town of Leonora from Perth but lost radio contact shortly
after its takeoff.
</P>
<P>
Flight recorders were not required on the light plane so
investigators would have to solve the mystery of what happened
after the plane took off with other information. 
</P>
