<DOCNO> XIE20000905.0278 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Populous Province Becoming Aging Society </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 5 (Xinhua) -- People above the age of 60
make 10.34 percent of China's most populous province of Henan,
indicating the province is entering the aging society.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest population sampling survey done by the
province, some 960,000 people in the hinterland province are over
the age of 60. And people above the age of 80 account for 1.71
percent of the 93 million people in the province.
</P>
<P>
Liu Junzhe, an expert on population, was shocked by the fast
growth of the aged population in the province, saying that in the
future there would be more senior citizens than young people in
the province.
</P>
<P>
Henan will become the home to the most numerous aged people in
China around the year 2040 when one out of every four to five
people will be 60 or above, he said.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the survey team suggested that the provincial
government work out policies as soon as possible to deal with the
issue of the elderly such as pension system, basic medicare, and a
social welfare system.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is the first municipality in China which has entered
the aging society. Fourteen municipalities and provinces,
including Beijing, Guangdong and Sichuan provinces, have also
joined the rank of aging society, which normally means people aged
above 60 make up more than 10 percent of the whole population.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
