<HEADLINE> S. Leone Hostage Takers Attack S.Leone Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The reports quoted military sources as saying that the rebels
or the West Side Boys had seized the village of Mgbini from pro-
government militia on Saturday, killing three militiamen.
</P>
<P>
"They are now in control of the area, trying to spread their
position along the Masiaka/Mile 91 highway," Sierra Leone Army
spokesman Major John Milton said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Relatives of the West Side Boys, meanwhile, spent a second day
with the hostage-takers at their Occra Hills base 50 kilometers
from Freetown, trying to persuade them to free the six British
soldiers and a Sierra Leonean soldier seized with them.
</P>
<P>
The West Side Boys seized 11 British soldiers, who had been
training a new Sierra Leone Army, on August 25. They freed five of
them on August 30 after an earlier visit by the relatives.
</P>
<P>
The West Side Boys, estimated to have a few hundred members,
are an offshoot of forces loyal to the junta that ruled from May
1997 to February 1998.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the rebels placed demands including the release of
their supporters and family, recognition by the Sierra Leone
government and the establishment of an interim government. The
Sierra Leone Government has rejected their demands. 
